National Meeting Marks World Women's Day
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 8 (KCNA) -- A national meeting was held at the People's Palace of Culture today to mark the 95th World Women's Day.
 Pak Sun Hui, chairwoman of the C.C., the Korean Democratic Women's Union, made a report at the meeting. She noted that international unity and solidarity of women have been strengthened in the efforts to liquidate imperialism and colonialism and achieve national independence and build socialism and great progress has been made in the development of the world women's movement in nearly one century after the world progressive women set March 8 as an international holiday of the working women the world over. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter said: The Juche-oriented Korean women's movement has covered a glorious path in the crucible of the Korean revolution crowded with heroic and epoch-making events under the wise guidance of the generals of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il represents the destiny of our country and nation and women as well as victory and his guidance serves as an eternal lifeline for the Korean women's movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the women should unite close around him to accelerate the general march for the Songun revolution and thus bring about a signal change in the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and contribute to the successful accomplishment of the revolutionary cause of Juche, she said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She urged the Korean women to open up a new phase for national reunification by fully realizing the three forms of cooperation?national independence, peace against war, and reunification and patriotism--in the idea of "By Our Nation Itself" and strengthen friendship and solidarity with all the progressive women of the world and vigorously struggle against the ever-more undisguised aggressive and arbitrary practices of the U.S. imperialists in the international arena. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the meeting were Vice-President of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly Yang Hyong Sop, Secretary of the C.C., the Workers' Party of Korea Kim Jung Rin, Chairperson of the C.C., the Chondoist Chongu Party Ryu Mi Yong and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also on hand were overseas Korean women staying in the socialist homeland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were women of various foreign embassies and international bodies here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the meeting the participants appreciated a performance given by the State Symphony Orchestra.

Methane Gas Lamp Developed in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 8 (KCNA) -- The Heat Engineering Institute under the Academy of Sciences of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea has developed a new kind of lamp using methane.
 The "Kwangmyong 2002-A"-branded lamp has been introduced in several units and rural dwelling houses in North and South Phyongan and North Hwanghae Provinces.
 The lamp, whose structure and operation are simple, can be applied to any forms of methane producers in rural communities and stock-farms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 One cubic meter of methane is enough for two lamps for 7-8 hours, each of which is as luminant as a 100-watt electric bulb. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It, with illumining elements made with alkali metals or rare-earth metallic oxide, produces no radioactive substances. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The lamp was highly appreciated by the International Red Cross in October Juche 93 (2004).

Kim Jong Il Receives Commemorative Medal from Putin
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 8 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK and supreme commander of the Korean People's Army, received a medal commemorating the 60th anniversary of the victory in the Great Patriotic War presented by Vladimir Vladimirovich Putin, president of the Russian Federation.
 A ceremony of conveying the medal took place in grand style Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il was present there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present were Pak Pong Ju, premier of the DPRK Cabinet, Chief of the General Staff of the KPA Kim Yong Chun, member of the DPRK National Defence Commission, Yon Hyong Muk, vice-chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, and Kang Sok Ju, first vice-minister of Foreign Affairs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Russian Ambassador to the DPRK Andrei Gennadiyevich Karlov and official diplomats of the embassy were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ambassador, upon the authorization, conveyed the medal to Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A child of the Russian embassy here presented a bouquet to him congratulating him on receiving the medal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He extended thanks to the Russian president for awarding the commemorative medal to him.
